The weekend is finally here and there are new releases to make it worthwhile. We have a list of 3 movies to look out for this weekend, for your watching pleasure: ‘Pokémon Detective Pikachu’ Release date: May 10, 2019 Cast: Justice Smith as Tim, Kathryn Newton as Lucy, plus Ken Watanabe, Suki Waterhouse, Ryan Reynolds, Omar Chaparro, Chris Geere, and Bill Nighy. Synopsis: The story starts when ace private eye Harry Goodman goes mysteriously missing, prompting his 21-year-old son Tim to find out what happened. Aiding in the investigation is Harry’s former Pokémon partner, Detective Pikachu: a hilariously wise-cracking, adorable super-sleuth who is a puzzlement even to himself. Finding that they are uniquely equipped to communicate with one another, Tim and Pikachu join forces on a thrilling adventure to unravel the tangled mystery. Chasing clues together through the neon-lit streets of Ryme City—a sprawling, modern metropolis where humans and Pokémon live side by side in a hyper-realistic live-action world—they encounter a diverse cast of Pokémon characters and uncover a shocking plot that could destroy this peaceful co-existence and threaten the whole Pokémon universe. The Hustle Release date: May 10, 2019 Cast: Anne Hathaway, Rebel Wilson, Tim Blake Nelson, Alex Sharp, Ingrid Oliver, Emma Davies, and Douggie McMeekin. Synopsis: In this hilarious comedy, Anne Hathaway and Rebel Wilson star as female scam artists, one low rent and the other high class, who team up to take down the dirty rotten men who have wronged them. Poms Release date: May 10, 2019. Cast: Diane Keaton, Jacki Weaver, Pam Grier, Charlie Tahan, Rhea Perlman, Celia Weston, Phyllis Somerville, Charli Tahan, Alisha Boe, and Bruce McGill. Synopsis: The film is about a woman who moves into a retirement community and starts a cheerleading squad with her fellow residents, proving that it’s never too late to follow your dreams.  N.B: All dates are US release dates.